ofthearch", "created": 1782828985670, "profile_picture": "fYN5qnn5z9Zd", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "www.supremecourt.gov", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/25pdf/24-43_2b35.pdf", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Supreme Court just told trannies to get fucked and compete with other men.", "last_comment_created": 1782828985670, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 0, "score_up": 32, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ATBhJ1fdP", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 20, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8706407, "raw_content": "If Barrett, Roberts, or one of the other 3 communists dies, we can overturn birthright citizenship now. All we need is ONE new justice. We now know we have 4 votes to overturn it. \r\n\r\nThis is actually remarkable progress. Birthright citizenship has been the rule for 150 years. Nobody seriously thought it was going to be overturned, many conservative lawyers were predicting it being upheld 9-0.\r\n\r\nTrump came within one vote of overturning it and is still just one vote away. Not long ago this was unthinkable.\r\n\r\nPeople blaming Trump for picking Barrett are kind of dumb btw. Yes, in hindsight she turned out to be a stupid bitch and a total disgrace to Scalia, who she was supposed to be a protege of. But basically every conservative was happy about the pick at the time. \r\n\r\nBecause of the situation at the time, Trump really had almost no choice but to pick her. Her voting record was great. She was politically popular. It seemed like a no brainer at the time.", "author": "STFUmuslimCUCKS", "created": 1782837985463, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "TrancePhreak", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Birthright shitizenship silver living ", "last_comment_created": 1782840498647, "content": "<p>If Barrett, Roberts, or one of the other 3 communists dies, we can overturn birthright citizenship now. All we need is ONE new justice. We now know we have 4 votes to overturn it.</p>\n<p>This is actually remarkable progress. Birthright citizenship has been the rule for 150 years. Nobody seriously thought it was going to be overturned, many conservative lawyers were predicting it being upheld 9-0.</p>\n<p>Trump came within one vote of overturning it and is still just one vote away. Not long ago this was unthinkable.</p>\n<p>People blaming Trump for picking Barrett are kind of dumb btw. Yes, in hindsight she turned out to be a stupid bitch and a total disgrace to Scalia, who she was supposed to be a protege of. But basically every conservative was happy about the pick at the time.</p>\n<p>Because of the situation at the time, Trump really had almost no choice but to pick her. Her voting record was great. She was politically popular. It seemed like a no brainer at the time.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 19, "score_up": 20, "is_edited": true, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": 